LD scores from UKBB, downloaded from https://pan.ukbb.broadinstitute.org/docs/ld


Variants included:  high-quality HapMap 3 variants that are 1) in autosomes, 2) not in the MHC region, 3) biallelic SNPs, 4) with INFO > 0.9, and 5) MAF > 1% in UKB and gnomAD genome/exome (if available).

Populations:
EUR = European ancestry
CSA = Central/South Asian ancestry
AFR = African ancestry
EAS = East Asian ancestry
MID = Middle Eastern ancestry
AMR = Admixed American ancestry

SNP locations in these files are on Build 37 of the genome.

Please see documentation on that site for details about these scores



